reviews.text:
yanno, this one is a little odd on my palette. The watermelon is good. The strawberry is good. It's bright and chilly, like it should be. And yet...there's an odd undercurrent. Somehow, some way, there's a bit of a nutty profile in here. I can't explain it, but it's there. This is like a tropical trail mix. On Ice.&#xD;
&#xD;
And I dig it!&#xD;
&#xD;
Severely tasty stuff. Made a batch for a friend without the ws-23 to make sure I wasn't losing my mind. He's the one who coined tropical trail mix as a descriptor. Think mebbe it's the wild melon's "rindiness" doing that?&#xD;
&#xD;
Regardless, this stuff is flat banging.
